name: Steve Bruce
summary: A woman in her 40s has been arrested on suspicion of child neglect following the death of Steve Bruce's four-month-old grandson, Madison Bruce. The baby was found dead at his home in Newcastle upon Tyne on Wednesday, October 12. The woman, who has not been named, was arrested on Thursday, October 13. She is currently in police custody and helping with the investigation. The cause of Madison's death is not yet known, but police say it is being treated as unexplained. Steve Bruce, the former manager of Newcastle United and Manchester United, has expressed his grief over the loss of his grandson. He said that Madison was a "beautiful, innocent baby" who will be "missed by everyone who knew him."

- **I / AM UNWRAPPED: Rewarding your fandom with Aston Martin Aramco prizes:** An Aston Martin Formula 1 team announces a rewards program for fans.

name: Daniel Kretinsky
summary: Daniel Kretinsky, a Czech billionaire, has received approval from the UK government to acquire Royal Mail. Kretinsky, known as the "Czech Sphinx" due to his secretive nature, has a history of investing in energy, media, and retail companies. His bid of £5.3 billion for Royal Mail has been met with mixed reactions, with some concerned about a foreign entity taking control of the iconic postal service. The takeover marks a significant departure for Royal Mail, which has been under British ownership for 500 years.
